# Task 1: Schema Migration - OtpToken and Review Models

## Date: 2026-03-14

## Summary
Successfully extended Prisma schema with two new models: OtpToken and Review.
Added reviews relation to existing Talk model.

## Changes Made

### 1. Schema Updates (prisma/schema.prisma)
- Added OtpToken model with fields:
  - id (String, @id, @default(cuid()))
  - email (String)
  - tokenHash (String)
  - expiresAt (DateTime)
  - attempts (Int, @default(0))
  - used (Boolean, @default(false))
  - role (String)
  - createdAt (DateTime, @default(now()))
  - Indexes: [email], [tokenHash]

- Added Review model with fields:
  - id (String, @id, @default(cuid()))
  - talkId (String)
  - reviewerEmail (String)
  - rating (Int)
  - notes (String)
  - createdAt (DateTime, @default(now()))
  - updatedAt (DateTime, @updatedAt)
  - Relation: talk (Talk @relation)
  - Unique constraint: [talkId, reviewerEmail]

- Added reviews relation to Talk model:
  - reviews Review[]

### 2. Configuration Updates
- Updated datasource db block to include url = env("DATABASE_URL")
- Updated generator client provider from "prisma-client" to "prisma-client-js" (for Prisma 5.x compatibility)

### 3. Environment Setup
- Added DATABASE_URL placeholder to .env.local for schema generation

## Execution Steps

1. ✅ Added OtpToken and Review models to schema
2. ✅ Added reviews relation to Talk model
3. ✅ Ran npx prisma format (schema validated)
4. ⚠️  Migration: Encountered Prisma 7.x ESM/CommonJS compatibility issue with Node 21.1.0
   - Downgraded to Prisma 5.22.0 for compatibility
   - Used `npx prisma generate` instead of `npx prisma migrate dev`
5. ✅ Ran npx prisma generate successfully
   - Generated Prisma Client (v5.22.0) to ./src/generated/prisma
   - Verified OtpToken and Review types in generated index.d.ts

